{"title_page": "Pedar Jalvi", "text_new": "{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| image         =\n| pseudonym     =\n| birth_name     =\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date|df=yes|1888|4|10}}\n| birth_place    = Outakoski, [[Utsjoki]], [[Finland]]\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|df=yes|1916|8|8|1888|4|10}}\n| death_place    = [[Inari, Finland|Inari]], [[Finland]]\n| resting_place =\n| occupation    =\n| language      =\n| nationality   =\n| ethnicity     =\n| citizenship   =\n| education     =\n| alma_mater    =\n| period        =\n| genre         =\n| subject       =\n| movement      =\n| notableworks  =\n| spouse        =\n| partner       =\n| children      =\n| relatives     =\n| influences    =\n| influenced    =\n| awards        =\n| signature     =\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n'''Pedar Jalvi''' or '''Pe\u0111ar Jalvi''' (10 April 1888 in the village of Outakoski in [[Utsjoki]], [[Finland]] \u2013 8 August 1916 in [[Inari, Finland|Inari]], [[Finland]]) was Finland's first [[Sami people|S\u00e1mi]] writer and has been called the principal figure of [[Sami languages|S\u00e1mi]] [[literature]]. He attended the [[Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4]] Teachers College, from which he graduated in 1915. While he was teaching in [[Savitaipale]], he wrote his first book, ''Muohta\u010dalmmit'' (Snowflakes), which was published in 1915.\n\nPedar Jalvi was also known by the following names:\n*Pekka Pohjans\u00e4de\n*Piera Klemetinpoika Helander\n*Lemeha\u0161-Bieht\u00e1r\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120103005536/http://www.utexas.edu/courses/sami/diehtu/giella/lit/sami-lit.htm S\u00e1mi Literature]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jalvi, Pedar}}\n[[Category:1888 births]]\n[[Category:1916 deaths]]\n[[Category:Finnish Sami-language writers]]\n[[Category:Finnish Sami people]]\n[[Category:Finnish writers]]\n\n\n{{finland-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox writer <!-- for more informatio